                <h1>Understanding Internet Censorship: Impacts & Implications</h1>
                <p>Internet censorship refers to the control or suppression of what can be accessed, viewed, or communicated on the internet. Governments and organizations often impose these restrictions to manage information flow, protect national security, or uphold social norms. However, this practice raises concerns about freedom of expression and access to information.</p>
